… 36 Lagos lawmakers also sign for him One of the governorship aspirants on the platform of the All Progressives Congress, APC, in Lagos, Dr. Femi Hamzat, has indicated his readiness to step down for Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu. Hamzat made this known during a press conference in Lagos on Saturday while urging his supporters to vote for Sanwo-Olu. In the same vein, members of the Lagos State House of Assembly adopted Babajide Sanwo-Olu as the candidate they will support in the coming governorship primaries of the state chapter of the APC. According to a statement by the Chairman of the House Committee on Information, Strategy and Security, Princess Adefunmilayo Tejuoso, the decision was taken at a Parliamentary meeting of the lawmakers which took place at Lateef Jakande auditorium on Saturday, a day before the governorship primaries of the party. The meeting was presided over by the Speaker of the House, Hon. Mudashiru Obasa. 36 members were present out of the 40 members of the House and all of them endorsed the decision and duly signed the statement announcing the decision. Hon. Segun Olulade and Abiodun Tobun both from Epe constituencies 1&2, the same place as Governor Akinwunmi Ambode were absent including Hon. Sikiru Osinowo who is said to be outside the country. The lawmakers stated that they were in agreement with the leadership of the party and the Governor’s Advisory Council (GAC) which had earlier endorsed Sanwo-olu for the governorship ticket.  